1
00:01:26,250 --> 00:01:35,000
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,259 --> 00:01:37,950
[Episode 22]

3
00:01:41,930 --> 00:01:43,500
Seems you're catching on.

4
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:46,009
As long as you want to learn,

5
00:01:46,509 --> 00:01:48,400
I will teach you

6
00:01:48,430 --> 00:01:50,360
everything without reservation.

7
00:01:51,150 --> 00:01:52,050
Mr. Cao,

8
00:01:52,450 --> 00:01:53,009
I'm here.

9
00:01:56,770 --> 00:01:58,140
Why are you early?

10
00:02:00,700 --> 00:02:01,360
Please carry on.

11
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:02,220
I'll come back later.

12
00:02:02,220 --> 00:02:02,810
No, no.

13
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:06,300
[Spirits Soaring High]

14
00:02:02,930 --> 00:02:03,750
Well,

15
00:02:03,980 --> 00:02:05,450
Uncle, I'll come back tomorrow.

16
00:02:05,450 --> 00:02:06,760
You do your business first.

17
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,150
Okay.

18
00:02:12,310 --> 00:02:13,130
Great acting.

19
00:02:18,190 --> 00:02:18,870
It's fine.

20
00:02:19,870 --> 00:02:20,750
He's my nephew.

21
00:02:27,460 --> 00:02:28,200
Thanks.

22
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:41,520
Let me give you an update.

23
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,630
I've been doing transportation lately.

24
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:44,470
It's legal.

25
00:02:45,090 --> 00:02:47,180
I bring in beef and mutton
from Inner Mongolia,

26
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:49,140
and supply them to restaurants.

27
00:02:49,340 --> 00:02:50,579
I keep some for myself,

28
00:02:50,579 --> 00:02:51,870
and also run a barbecue stall.

29
00:02:51,870 --> 00:02:52,870
Isn't that great?

30
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:55,250
Put in a good word for me with your sis.

31
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:55,990
No problem.

32
00:02:56,650 --> 00:02:58,650
What about your construction team?

33
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:02,710
There's less work than before.

34
00:03:03,180 --> 00:03:03,980
That won't do.

35
00:03:05,090 --> 00:03:06,290
You have to work hard.

36
00:03:06,460 --> 00:03:07,750
Work your tail off.

37
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:09,500
I'll see when my sis

38
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:10,760
will let you come back.

39
00:03:10,780 --> 00:03:11,310
Shengli.

40
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,590
I'm being honest with you.

41
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:15,320
Why are you being so sarcastic?

42
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,300
Surviving out here

43
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:19,130
isn't like being a big screenwriter.

44
00:03:19,130 --> 00:03:21,240
You can't be dead broke one night,

45
00:03:21,310 --> 00:03:22,540
and rich the next...

46
00:03:22,970 --> 00:03:23,400
Wait.

47
00:03:24,740 --> 00:03:26,270
What's the meaning of this?

48
00:03:26,910 --> 00:03:28,370
I-It's...

49
00:03:28,620 --> 00:03:29,430
It's not that easy?

50
00:03:29,430 --> 00:03:30,490
It's not that easy?

51
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:33,630
I think it's quite easy for you.

52
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,130
You really

53
00:03:35,410 --> 00:03:36,860
don't ever want to go back, do you?

54
00:03:36,860 --> 00:03:39,060
Last time you were crying your eyes out,

55
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,829
saying how much you missed your daughter,

56
00:03:40,829 --> 00:03:42,490
and how much you missed my sis.

57
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:44,810
It's a pity you're not an actor.

58
00:03:49,030 --> 00:03:51,070
Can you spare a thought for me?

59
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:53,430
You think I like doing this?

60
00:03:54,079 --> 00:03:55,300
People yell in my face every day.

61
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,020
You think I like that?

62
00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:57,370
I'm just trying to make some money

63
00:03:57,370 --> 00:03:58,560
to pay off the debt.

64
00:03:58,620 --> 00:03:59,280
Once I pay off the debt,

65
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,940
I'll stop doing this for sure.

66
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:01,960
I swear to you.

67
00:04:02,470 --> 00:04:04,530
If I do this again, I'm a son of a bitch.

68
00:04:08,620 --> 00:04:10,960
You'll stop once the debt is paid?

69
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:12,890
I definitely will.

70
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,300
It's already paid.

71
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:17,209
Mr. Big Screenwriter.

72
00:04:17,310 --> 00:04:18,060
The debt is paid

73
00:04:18,060 --> 00:04:18,930
just because you said so?

74
00:04:18,930 --> 00:04:19,560
My sis sold

75
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,600
the house her dad left her.

76
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,390
She originally didn't want me

77
00:04:30,390 --> 00:04:31,420
to tell you this.

78
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:45,580
At 10:00 a.m. tomorrow,

79
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:47,920
she will be waiting for you at the store.

80
00:04:59,650 --> 00:05:01,790
[CHUN LAI JIE]

81
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:21,810
I've searched for you
over thousands of miles.

82
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:26,540
But you don't even care.

83
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:34,190
You don't seem to be in my dreams.

84
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:39,570
But in my dreams, you are my only one.

85
00:05:53,810 --> 00:05:54,780
Are you hungry?

86
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,730
I'll make you a bowl of noodles.

87
00:06:15,570 --> 00:06:18,730
[Endeavor]

88
00:06:17,770 --> 00:06:18,500
Out of money?

89
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:27,260
[Endeavor]

90
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:27,640
Did you really split 20-80
with Zhuang Zhuang?

91
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:30,280
No, 50-50.

92
00:06:31,420 --> 00:06:33,360
Before Zhuang Zhuang
took classes last year,

93
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,770
she paid the teacher a large amount

94
00:06:34,770 --> 00:06:35,970
of owed tuition fees.

95
00:06:35,970 --> 00:06:39,540
[Endeavor]

96
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:38,090
She also sent some money home,

97
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,500
so she doesn't have much left.

98
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,560
I'm about the same.

99
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,460
I sent some home,

100
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:43,800
recorded a song,

101
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:45,640
and paid half a year's rent.

102
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,159
If we don't make money
for another 2 months,

103
00:06:48,159 --> 00:06:49,930
I'll be living a hard life
with you, buddy.

104
00:06:49,930 --> 00:06:50,560
Save it.

105
00:06:50,630 --> 00:06:52,170
Don't live a hard life with me.

106
00:06:52,170 --> 00:06:55,400
[Endeavor]

107
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:55,280
You can't handle it.

108
00:06:58,310 --> 00:06:59,540
We can't go on like this.

109
00:06:59,540 --> 00:07:00,870
We need to think of a way.

110
00:07:01,190 --> 00:07:02,130
What way?

111
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:04,240
There's no ready work for us to do.

112
00:07:05,390 --> 00:07:06,430
There is a way.

113
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,090
Look for him.

114
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,090
You call him.

115
00:07:23,220 --> 00:07:25,360
I care about my pride.

116
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:30,880
Pride? But you're childhood friends.

117
00:07:31,690 --> 00:07:32,450
Care about your pride?

118
00:07:32,450 --> 00:07:34,120
If you care about pride,
don't try to make money.

119
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:36,450
Just pretend he's your childhood friend.

120
00:07:36,450 --> 00:07:37,909
Just invite him to dinner.

121
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,520
We'll talk when he gets here.

122
00:07:41,180 --> 00:07:42,909
Stop pressing the calculator.

123
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,159
It's bad luck.

124
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:51,980
The signal is bad in this basement.

125
00:07:53,770 --> 00:07:54,430
I haven't played

126
00:07:54,430 --> 00:07:55,630
that thing for years.

127
00:07:55,930 --> 00:07:57,659
I'm busy with other things now.

128
00:07:58,250 --> 00:07:59,620
Ask someone else.

129
00:08:00,690 --> 00:08:01,930
No, I'm really

130
00:08:01,930 --> 00:08:03,460
busy with other things now.

131
00:08:03,890 --> 00:08:04,890
I don't have time.

132
00:08:05,570 --> 00:08:06,060
Okay.

133
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:07,300
I'll call you back later.

134
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:08,060
I'm hanging up.

135
00:08:08,060 --> 00:08:09,520
Thank you, Director Wang.

136
00:08:10,810 --> 00:08:12,750
-What a waste of my phone bill.
-Slow down.

137
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:15,270
You are Liangliang's
childhood friend, right?

138
00:08:15,270 --> 00:08:16,100
Look at him,

139
00:08:16,540 --> 00:08:18,500
young and promising.

140
00:08:19,930 --> 00:08:21,000
Ma Xiaojun.

141
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:23,020
This is Guo Zongbao, an actor.

142
00:08:23,220 --> 00:08:24,040
Hello.

143
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:25,100
An actor?

144
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:25,740
Actor, yes.

145
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:27,200
A guest actor. I had lines.

146
00:08:28,390 --> 00:08:30,060
I'm meeting a star.

147
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,860
I was just saying you looked a bit...

148
00:08:31,860 --> 00:08:33,049
a bit familiar.
You must have starred in...

149
00:08:33,049 --> 00:08:33,530
Really?

150
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:37,360
Starred in...

151
00:08:38,870 --> 00:08:39,799
S-Starred in...

152
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:41,000
I brought you guys

153
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:41,850
some tea,

154
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,289
pastries, and snacks.

155
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,460
Let me think about it.

156
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:45,310
Have a seat.

157
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:47,020
Why haven't you

158
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,860
moved to another place yet?

159
00:08:48,860 --> 00:08:50,630
It's cozy here.

160
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:52,200
We are used to living here.

161
00:08:52,910 --> 00:08:54,240
Why did you call me here?

162
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:58,170
To make money.

163
00:08:58,530 --> 00:09:00,130
Didn't we just make a sum of money?

164
00:09:00,130 --> 00:09:01,430
We kind of spent

165
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:03,300
all the money we made before.

166
00:09:03,740 --> 00:09:05,130
What did you do? You spent it so quickly.

167
00:09:05,130 --> 00:09:07,120
We had to spend money on everything.

168
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,480
So it's gone.

169
00:09:08,790 --> 00:09:10,790
If you need money, come to Mr. Lucky.

170
00:09:11,980 --> 00:09:13,460
Find Lucky, get lucky.

171
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,800
You've come to the right person.

172
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:18,180
But my luck is bad now, too.

173
00:09:19,270 --> 00:09:20,600
It's not the season yet.

174
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:21,770
In China and Russia...

175
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:23,030
You see, it's the off-season now.

176
00:09:23,030 --> 00:09:24,030
It has to be colder.

177
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:25,320
Now I mainly

178
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:28,000
do some middleman work
for the surrounding factories

179
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,120
to make some money.

180
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,010
But it's a one-person job.

181
00:09:33,410 --> 00:09:35,010
You guys gotta think of a way.

182
00:09:35,460 --> 00:09:36,390
This economy...

183
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,110
This...

184
00:09:40,910 --> 00:09:43,170
Do you know how expensive a phone call is?

185
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:48,500
You, a screenwriter...

186
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:50,940
An actor...

187
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:52,620
A...

188
00:09:54,030 --> 00:09:55,090
Saxophone player.

189
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,380
Saxophone player.

190
00:10:00,530 --> 00:10:01,330
Wait a minute.

191
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:01,910
What's the matter?

192
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:02,910
No, wait a minute.

193
00:10:10,180 --> 00:10:11,860
Director. Director Wang, it's me.

194
00:10:11,860 --> 00:10:12,750
Lucky Ma.

195
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:13,750
Yes.

196
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:15,290
What was the matter you mentioned before?

197
00:10:15,290 --> 00:10:16,690
Could you say that again?

198
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:18,370
Yes, what do you need?

199
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,820
You're looking for a band?

200
00:10:24,210 --> 00:10:26,010
Okay, I'll arrange it for you.

201
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,410
I'll reply to you later.

202
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:28,560
I'm hanging up.

203
00:10:29,330 --> 00:10:30,850
Hey, exactly 59 seconds.

204
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,170
Let's do band gigs.

205
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:35,360
No problem.

206
00:10:35,460 --> 00:10:37,550
What's a gig?

207
00:10:37,620 --> 00:10:38,250
A gig is when

208
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:40,240
singers and dancers

209
00:10:40,460 --> 00:10:41,260
come together

210
00:10:41,270 --> 00:10:43,010
to form a moving band.

211
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,650
You'll travel from city to city to perform

212
00:10:44,650 --> 00:10:46,260
at factory parties,

213
00:10:46,290 --> 00:10:48,290
celebrations,

214
00:10:48,530 --> 00:10:50,580
weddings, funerals,

215
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:51,390
and baby showers.

216
00:10:51,390 --> 00:10:52,930
You perform place by place,

217
00:10:53,410 --> 00:10:54,410
sing place by place,

218
00:10:54,410 --> 00:10:55,340
make money place by place,

219
00:10:55,340 --> 00:10:56,360
and share the money show by show.

220
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:57,580
It's perfect for us.

221
00:10:58,770 --> 00:10:59,530
That works.

222
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:00,050
Sounds good.

223
00:11:00,050 --> 00:11:00,390
This will work.

224
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:00,920
Exactly.

225
00:11:01,010 --> 00:11:02,150
Don't you all have specialties?

226
00:11:02,150 --> 00:11:03,120
Aren't you playing the...

227
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:03,780
Saxophone.

228
00:11:03,820 --> 00:11:04,080
Yes.

229
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:05,030
I remember when you were young,

230
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:05,550
you could play the...

231
00:11:05,550 --> 00:11:06,220
Guitar.

232
00:11:06,910 --> 00:11:08,130
And the young lady can...

233
00:11:08,130 --> 00:11:08,650
Sing.

234
00:11:09,890 --> 00:11:10,510
Bro, what about you?

235
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:11,550
I'm an actor.

236
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:13,160
I can also sing Yu Opera.

237
00:11:13,850 --> 00:11:18,470
Big Brother Liu's words are...

238
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:19,790
-Bro.
-It’s too...

239
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:20,770
Your voice cracked.

240
00:11:20,770 --> 00:11:21,270
Is it okay?

241
00:11:21,270 --> 00:11:22,410
I think when we get to the right place,

242
00:11:22,410 --> 00:11:23,870
you might be loved

243
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:25,840
by middle-aged and elderly women.

244
00:11:25,870 --> 00:11:27,060
Sounds good.

245
00:11:27,340 --> 00:11:29,200
Doesn't Ranran know how to dance?

246
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,000
Don't bother her.

247
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,120
She's a big star now.

248
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,360
She can't go gigging with us.

249
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,320
Come on.

250
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,250
Let Zhuang Zhuang ask her.

251
00:11:35,250 --> 00:11:36,050
If she is free,

252
00:11:36,050 --> 00:11:36,910
she can join us.

253
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,270
We can all make money together.

254
00:11:38,270 --> 00:11:39,360
Let's do it together.

255
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:40,690
What are you going to do?

256
00:11:41,010 --> 00:11:42,340
Well, if all else fails, I can

257
00:11:42,340 --> 00:11:43,290
write a sketch for them.

258
00:11:43,290 --> 00:11:44,020
Sounds good.

259
00:11:44,290 --> 00:11:45,150
I think you are quite smart.

260
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:47,560
Why don't you be in charge of

261
00:11:47,580 --> 00:11:48,240
contact matters?

262
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,720
How about being the general agent?

263
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:50,830
Sure.

264
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:52,570
That's great.

265
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:53,430
Right?

266
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:55,270
Now we have a full team, don't we?

267
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:56,670
We've got everything...

268
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:59,100
All ready now.

269
00:11:59,170 --> 00:11:59,750
How great is that?

270
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:00,640
Ma Xiaojun

271
00:12:00,820 --> 00:12:02,080
has never dropped the ball

272
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,480
since we were kids.

273
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:04,570
I know.

274
00:12:04,790 --> 00:12:05,850
Really.

275
00:12:06,050 --> 00:12:07,550
We've been through life and death together

276
00:12:07,550 --> 00:12:09,470
in Russia, after all.

277
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:10,270
Yes, yes.

278
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:13,500
Our performance group

279
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:14,960
needs a name, right?

280
00:12:16,580 --> 00:12:17,250
You tell me.

281
00:12:17,670 --> 00:12:18,730
Let me think of one.

282
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:20,980
It should be called...

283
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:22,680
Let's call it...

284
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:25,290
I remember what you acted in!

285
00:12:25,290 --> 00:12:25,750
What?

286
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:27,080
I suddenly remembered it.

287
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,070
You acted in...

288
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,780
He acted in that thing...

289
00:12:29,890 --> 00:12:31,280
Called...

290
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:32,600
"Transformers." No.

291
